\section{Citations}
\label{Section 3}

Remember to give the title of all the articles in references and
inclusive page numbers in each reference. This is a special
requirement of ASR. We request authors to provide at least three 
names before "et al." in multi-authored papers.

\begin{itemize}
\item Parenthetical: \verb|\citep{WB96}| produces \citep{WB96}.
\item Textual: \verb|\citet{WB96}| produces \citet{WB96}.
\item An affix and part of a reference:
   \verb|\citep[e.g.][Ch. 2]{WB96}|
   produces \citep[e.g.][Ch. 2]{WB96}.
\end{itemize}

